5:
Now then, I present to you a treaty
between Palpebra and Shibuya. Feel
free to confirm the contents yourself.
9:
...Well, what do you think, Suizen?
Regis?
15:
No problems here. Everything is
exactly as discussed.
20:
Rest assured that no tricks or spells
have been deployed either.
24:
All right... Then let us proceed. We
look forward to working with you.
29:
And we you. Let this be the
beginning of a beautiful friendship,
Mayor of Shibuya.
44:
Enough of that... This is just
provisional title. It's mostly
decorative.
48:
Come on, I thought you were past
lying to us...
56:
If it was mere decoration, we
would've strung you up like a
puppet, no?
61:
Precisely! You've been moving on
your own this whole time, my good
man. You're a real boy—I mean,
mayor!
71:
Looks like you guys met before I got
back.
76:
That we did. Light asked us to check
in on this new Shibuya joint, so we
went to have a look.
81:
Many were in physical and mental
shock after having their worldview
shattered. There was a risk of
widespread panic setting in as well.
83:
However, we were able to avoid
such a situation due to Seiji's hard
work and powers.
87:
I just wanted to help. My powers
help me restore people and objects
to a previous state.
90:
Who would've thought it would lead
to a career in politics...
95:
Thanks, Mr. Takamori, and... Sorry if
we were asking too much of you.
99:
Oh, that's all right. I'm actually
thrilled to see my students asking
me for help.
114:
Well, that's not good. A politician
needs blinding charisma if he wants
to get the job done.
120:
We're all here for you. Please do your
best.
129:
Oh, here you are. Having a nice chat
with your students?
132:
Don't tell me you forgot about our
engagement after this.
137:
Ah, is it that time already?
Apologies, everyone, but Regis and I
need to go.
143:
Hehe, we'll be borrowing your
teacher for a little bit.
151:
Don't know, but probably nothing
good... Why aren't you joining them,
Suizen?
155:
It appears to me that their plans
aren't exactly child-friendly.
161:
Wait, you mean like... something
naughty? No fair! I wanna go!
166: Sho, have you ever heard of subtlety?
172:
Well, here's to a job well-done.
Lemme pour you a drink, Teach.
177:
Oh, thank you... Ah, that should be
enough.
183:
Mm-mm! What a robust flavor! To
think this delicate drink comes from
humble rice!
191:
Indeed it is. I can't imagine life
without taste buds now... Not that I
was alive to begin with!
196:
Marina, you must try the meat
dishes here. We should order before
we've had too many drinks. It tastes
much better that way!
201:
Yeah, yeah. Hey, barkeep! Get me
something tall and dark, on the
double!
206:
Light, I believe they also have
carbonated beverages.
212:
S-surely one sip of alcohol would be
all right...
216:
Us adults always have our guards
up around the youngsters, don't we?
Well, tonight we can all loosen up a
bit.
223:
You know... I was never good at
going out for drinks with coworkers.
227:
Oh, my bad. Didn't mean to drag
you out against your will.
231:
No, not at all... I'm actually enjoying
myself.
233:
I've always wanted to be a cool
adult like everyone here...
237:
Whoa there, Teach. Sounds like
you're already a bit buzzed.
241:
Nothing wrong with that. It's much
better to share stories with a fine
beverage in hand.
245:
Speaking of stories, we've been
meaning to ask you...
250: What was Alk like as a kid?
254:
Hey, no fair! I wanna hear about Alk
too!
259:
So THAT'S why we went out tonight,
huh?
263:
Well, let's see... He was certainly a
strong-willed boy, but...
266: He always seemed a bit lonely...
